Textual XML is the default format for XML document. We considered here XML documents as defined by the
XML 1.0 [
] and the
Namespaces in XML 1.0 [
] specifications (XML 1.1 introduces only marginal changes and the results of our study mostly apply).

Fast Infoset is a binary XML format, specified by the
ITU-T rec. X.891 | ISO/IEC 24824-1 standard [
]. This format drops the textual representation of XML documents to replace it by a binary representation, enabling a more compact encoding of XML documents.
